  "2026-07-17T13:31:47.168Z",codex-root,"GitHub reconciliation: GH-578 remains the canonical external issue for this item and there are no open PRs or dependency/secret alerts. The implementation bundle directly resolves its shared-semantics requirement; final closure will follow parity tests, package acceptance, and PR review evidence."
  "2026-07-17T13:47:21.330Z",codex-root,"Final implementation evidence: context, next, and list-blocked consume one public SDK actionability definition; 76 linked parity tests pass. Fresh installed tarball returned demo-lifecycle and status-open demo-deploy from list-blocked with blocked_semantics=status_or_dependency, while context summary.blocked=2. Full suite passes 5,798 tests and exact 100/100/100/100 coverage; lint/static/package/security gates pass."
  "2026-07-17T14:12:22.689Z",codex-root,"Pre-push Greptile review 5843a507-bc02-480c-b73f-b95c37e34b46: fixed live-blocker display precedence so an open edge blocker wins over a resolved legacy scalar, and retired no-active-blocker sentinels are excluded from shared actionability in scalar and edge forms. Focused parity tests pass 78/78; full repository passes 5,800 tests at exact 100/100/100/100; typecheck, ESLint, zero clones, static quality, docstrings, package boundary, and token budget pass."
notes[1]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-17T10:10:38.866Z",maintainer-agent,"Code evidence (2026-07-17 pass #95): context summary blocked counter at src/cli/commands/context.ts:1126-1132 increments only via isBlockedStatus(desc.status, statusRegistry) — status-only, no dependency-edge awareness; agenda ranking helpers at :675-682/:717 are likewise status-registry-driven. list-blocked is a status-filter list variant registered at src/cli/register-list-query.ts:656 (one of the 8 variants pm-pfqi consolidates). pm next's edge-aware definition (open_blocker_count from blocked_by deps, shipped for GH-489/pm-l0bu in PR#502) is the semantics to adopt. pm stats reports generic by-status buckets (honest labeling, NOT in scope). Fix belongs in a shared blocked-semantics helper consumed by next + context + list-blocked so pm-pfqi/pm-kcs4 consolidations inherit it."
